    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="330"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 (D) Regulations/3275: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-16T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 16, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>352. For Boal from Feis. Please confirm by telegraph the Department’s
                    understanding that Douglas’ letter to Wiechers<note n="45" xml:id="d330fn45"
                        >Luciano Wiechers, economic adviser of the Bank of Mexico, and Mexican
                        representative in the export control discussions.</note> is dated July 15,
                    1941 and that the decree establishing export control was actually signed on July
                    10 and published on July 15<note n="46" xml:id="d330fn46">On July 18 the
                        Department received confirmation of its understanding. The decree and
                        letter, which constitute agreement, were published in the newspaper <hi
                            rend="italic">El Nacional</hi> on July 15, 1941.</note> in the form
                    transmitted to the Department in your 301 of July 11, 3 p.m. [Feis.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
